en_127563_0	Pivithuru Hela Urumaya (PHU) General Secretary Udaya Gammanpila yesterday (01) emphasized that he was not engaged in a project to form a new political party.
en_127563_1	Speaking at a press conference, Gammanpila stated that the Sri Lanka Freedom Party (SLFP) members who are opposed to President Sirisena's policy of surrendering the party to the UNP were planning to form a new party.
en_127563_2	The Pivithuru Hela Urumaya is engaged in an attempt to form a new alliance as an alternative to the United People's Freedom Alliance, which is now a dying entity, Gammanpila added.
en_127563_3	However, the official launch of the new alliance has been postponed indefinitely, he added, saying that it will be formed once the government calls for the Local Government Elections which are long overdue.
en_127563_4	He expressed confidence in former President Mahinda Rajapaksa accepting the leadership of this new alliance.
